      <div class="twitter-banner-container">

      <script>
       $( document ).ready(function() {

      });
      </script>
      <script>
       function TwitterSetup(WidgetId) {
            var config1 = {
                "id": WidgetId,
                "domId": 'example1',
                "maxTweets": 6,
                "enableLinks": true,
                "showUser": true,
                "showTime": false,
                "showRetweet": true,
                "customCallback": handleTweets,
                "showInteraction": false
            };
            twitterFetcher.fetch(config1);
        }

        function handleTweets(tweets) {
            // Decode tweets
            $.each(tweets, function (index, value) {
                var tweet = '<div>' + value + '</div>';
                
                // BT 112315 Hack. Author node coming from twitter does not contain src attribute for images.
                // Either this changed in the Twitter API and Twitter Fetcher needs an update,
                // Or we have responsive code somewhere to dynamically take attribute data-src-1x or data-src-2x
                // as the src and it has stopped working (probably also because of a Twitter API change.)
                // If the real problem is discovered and corrected, revert this code.
                
                var img = $(tweet).children('.user').find('[data-scribe="element:avatar"]')[0];
                $(img).attr('src', $(img).attr('data-src-1x'));
                var avatar = img.outerHTML;
               
                var username = $(tweet).children('.user').find('[data-scribe="element:name"]').html();
				var userlink = $(tweet).children('.user').find('[data-scribe="element:user_link"]').attr('href');
                var screen_name = $(tweet).children('.user').find('[data-scribe="element:screen_name"]').html();
                var content = $(tweet).children('.tweet').html();
                var html = '';
                html += '<div class="tweet">';
                html += '   <div class="tweet-image"><a href="' + userlink + '" target="_blank">' + avatar + '</a></div>';
                html += '   <div class="tweet-user"><strong>' + username + '</strong>' + screen_name + '</div>';
                html += '   <div class="tweet-contents">' + content + '</div>';
                html += '</div>';
                $(html).appendTo('#tweets');
            });

            // Init Slider
            $('#tweets').slick({
                autoplay: true,
                autoplaySpeed: 6000,
                dots: false,
                arrows: false,
                speed: 600,
                slidesToShow: 2,
                slidesToScroll: 2,
                responsive: [
                  {
                      breakpoint: 960,
                      settings: {
                          slidesToShow: 1,
                          slidesToScroll: 1
                      }
                  }]
            });
        }
      </script>
     </div>
